      "text": "Spurs – I believe that riders shouldn’t wear spurs until they have a stable leg. You can’t maintain a stable leg until you have self control and you can’t have that until you have self carriage. I have witnessed riders being urged to use spurs by their trainers because their horse is lazy. It doesn’t work. Spurs are for finessing leg aids, not for punishing the horse with legs the rider can’t control. At one yard that recommended this approach the horses all had scars on their sides. An overactive, clinging leg can create enough damage without spurs. If you are wearing patches off your horse’s coat it is time to stop and think and change your riding.",
